==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ovulist
<hw>O"vu*list</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A
believer in the theory (called <xex>encasement theory</xex>), current
during the last century, that the egg was the real animal germ, and that
at the time of fecundation the spermatozoa simply gave the impetus which
caused the unfolding of the egg, in which all generations were inclosed
one within the other. Also called <altname>ovist</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ovulite</ent>⟦br⟧
